Reserva Florestal Ducke, Manaus-Itacoatiara, km 26. Floresta de Vertente. Árvore. Sapopemas muito pequenas= base dilatada. Casca externa marrom-avermelhada, raspando fendida (fendas rasas (0,1) estreitas (0,1), distanciadas de 0,5 cm-00,8 cm, contínuas e distribuídas por toda a circunferência do fuste. Desprende em retículos irregulares que esfarelam facilmente na mao. Casca morta marrom-calra, facilmente destacável da viva. Casca via arroseada (0,3 cm) dificil de separar do alburno bege amarelado a nao ser pela exudaçao leve de látex branco-creme, aquoso em pequenina quantidade.

Parque Nacional y Area de Manejo Integrado """"Serranía del Iñao"""". Comunidad Ticucha. Pendiente inferior de la Serranía del Iñao. Estribaciones colinadas. Bosque decíduo 25 m de altura. Parque Nacional y Area de Manejo Integrado """"Serranía del Iñao"""". Comunidad Ticucha. Serranías intermedias de la Serranía del Iñao. Pendiente media 40% de inclinación. Parque Nacional y Area de Manejo Integrado """"Serranía del Iñao"""". Comunidad Ticucha. Margen del Río Tayarendita. Entre colinas intermedias de la serranía del Iñao. Subiendo a la serranía. Bosque semidecíduo. Dosel de 20 m de altura, con una maxima de 25 m. Sotobosque ralo, con varias especies espinosas.

Parque Nacional y Area de Manejo Integrado """"Serranía del Iñao"""". Comunidad Ticucha. Subiendo la Serranía del Iñao, siguiendo aguas arriba la quebrada de Jarca Mayu Grande. Pendiente media Bosque semidecíduo, dosel superior 18 m, altura máxina 25 m. Dominan varias especies de Lauraceae.

Permanent one-hectare forest inventory plot: """"Parcela Yunkumas"""". Trees > 10 cm DBH tagged and measured.

""""Huayra Pata"""" - - Major ruin discovery of large fortelezas, irrigation canals  and mysterious foundations cover this  ridge which is 2 km NE of the mouth of  the Río Aguilani mouth at Lakachaka,  and 2 km S. of the junction of the Río  Mikhailpurhua and Río Aguada. 22 km N.  of Choquetanga.  Area of ancient ruins which has been  overgrazed, burned and generally raped  into  semi-barren  grassland  with  some  small  shrubs.  Collected  bordering  woodlanads  and  mattorales

""""Mikailpurhua"""" - - If one follows the trail from Laka Chaka at the mouth of the Río Aguilani on the way to Khora, about 4 hours on foot (3.5 km crow flies) to the NNE one crosses two rivers. The north fork is the Río Aguada, the south fork is the Mikhailpurhua. 24 km N of Choquetanga. Very diverse riverine forest with everything from Sorocea to Boehmeria. Semi ever-green.

""""Parillada"""" - - This is an area of two ruined huts near the only spring on the ridge between the Río Isi Taxaña and Río Quenhuani (the former not on a map, the later misplaced where the former actually is). Area of newly discovered (today) agricultural terraces following a ridge down through head high grasses with scattered Bombaceae trees, to a newly discovered forteleza above the Río Isi Taxaña which is covered in a tangle of thorn scrub.
